stats.name: errors

stats.description: The number of times the ball is dropped or passes by the catcher.

stats.description: The number of times a fielder is involved in an out when the fielder is not the putouter.

stats.name: outfieldAssists
stats.description: The number of times an outfielder fielder is involved in an out when the fielder is not the putouter.

stats.name: pickoffs
stats.description: The number of times that a pitcher or catcher throws over and picks off a baserunner.

stats.name: putouts
stats.description: The number of times the fielder tags or forces the out of a baserunner.

stats.name: outsOnField

stats.name: triplePlays
stats.description: The number of times that a fielder is involved in a triple play.

stats.name: extraBases

stats.name: catcherThirdInningsPlayed

stats.name: catcherCaughtStealing
stats.description: The number of times a catcher throws a baserunner trying to steal a base.

stats.name: catcherStolenBasesAllowed
stats.description: The number of stolen bases that a catcher allows.

stats.name: catcherEarnedRuns
stats.description: The number of runs allowed by the catcher that aren't the result of an error or passed ball.

stats.name: isQualified

stats.description: Whether a player qualifies a catcher.

stats.name: isQualifiedPitcher
stats.description: Whether a player qualifies as a pitcher.

stats.name: successfulChances
stats.description: The number of outs involved in calculated by assists plus putouts.

stats.name: totalChances
stats.description: The number of chances a fielder has to make an out calculated by assists plus putouts plus errors.

stats.name: fullInningsPlayed
stats.description: The number of fully completed innings by a fielder.

stats.name: partInningsPlayed
stats.description: The number of at least partial innings played by a fielder.

stats.name: fieldingPct
stats.description: The percentage of plays made by a fielder given the total number of chances.

stats.name: rangeFactor
stats.description: The estimation of how much field a fielder can cover.

stats.name: zoneRating
stats.description: The metric used to estimate the ability of a fielder to defend a zone on the field.

stats.name: catcherERA

articles.headline: Raleigh hits MLB-best 44th homer and Rodríguez connects twice as streaking Mariners top Rays 7-4
articles.description: — Cal Raleigh launched his major league-leading 44th home run, Julio Rodríguez went deep twice and the surging Seattle Mariners defeated the Tampa Bay Rays 7-4 on Saturday night after <a...

articles.headline: Shohei Ohtani slugs 40th home run of season for Dodgers
articles.description: Shohei Ohtani hit his 40th home run of the season Saturday night, the fourth time the Dodgers' two-way star has hit the mark in his career.

images.name: Shohei Ohtani hammers his 40th homer of the season
images.caption: Shohei Ohtani clubs his 40th home run to pad the Dodgers' lead against the Blue Jays.

articles.headline: Machado's failed hidden ball trick costs one run in Padres win
articles.description: Padres third baseman Manny Machado tried a hidden-ball trick against the Boston Red Sox and it ended up costing San Diego a run.

images.name: Padres balk in a run on Manny Machado's failed hidden ball trick
images.caption: Manny Machado tries to fake out the Red Sox with a hidden ball trick, but Wandy Peralta is on the rubber which balks in a run.

articles.headline: Mariners beat Rays on Ichiro's jersey retirement night
articles.description: Cal Raleigh hammers his 44th home run vs. the Rays as the Mariners honor Ichiro in a 7-4 win.

images.name: Mariners beat Rays on Ichiro's jersey retirement night
images.caption: Cal Raleigh hammers his 44th home run vs. the Rays as the Mariners honor Ichiro in a 7-4 win.

articles.headline: Ichiro Suzuki joins Mariners legends with No. 51 retirement
articles.description: The Mariners retired the iconic No. 51 on Saturday, honoring Ichiro Suzuki in a pregame ceremony at T-Mobile Park before facing the Rays.

images.name: Ichiro [600x600]
images.caption: Like Ken Griffey Jr. before him, Ichiro Suzuki said Saturday he's "also damn proud to be a Seattle Mariner."

articles.headline: Laureano singles in Bogaerts in the 10th as the Padres walk-off the Red Sox, 5-4
articles.description: — Ramón Laureano singled in Xander Bogaerts from second base with no outs in the 10th inning and the San Diego Padres beat the Boston Red Sox 5-4 on Saturday night.

images.name: Padres win via walk off in extra innings
images.caption: Ramon Laureano hits a walk-off to give the Padres 5-4 victory.
